page.title: 11Wild Life
page.content: PLANTS Near the tors are many types of grasses such as purple moor grass and red fescue.Heather, gorse, tormentil, navelwort and bilberry are also found. Bracken is everywhere. Liverworts and mosses are in the crevices of such rock piles as Pew Tor. Filmy fern and Royal fern, of which there is a limited distribution in Britain, grow in the Walkham valley. Foxgloves, campion,bluebells, primroses, nettle, wild scabious, wild roses, clover and violets grow in their season.There are garden escapes and rhododendrons in the plantations. ANIMALS Sparrows, tits, robins, finches, pigeons, blackbirds, buzzards, barn and screech owls, skylarks, magpies and kestrels have been seen as have rabbits, mink, foxes and squirrels.
